1) “Bias” filter on a higher timeframe (default = 5m)

It only looks for longs if the 5-minute chart is bullish:

Price is above VWAP (5m)

EMA(9) is above EMA(21) (5m)

It only looks for shorts if the 5-minute chart is bearish:

Price is below VWAP (5m)

EMA(9) is below EMA(21) (5m)

This prevents you from taking random counter-trend scalps.

2) “Trigger” on your entry timeframe (you’ll typically use 1m)

Once bias is bullish, it waits for a pullback + reclaim:

Long scalp trigger (1m):

Price pulls back to EMA9 (or EMA21 if you choose that), then

Price reclaims EMA9 (the candle closes back above EMA9)

Short scalp trigger (1m):

Price pulls back up to EMA9/EMA21, then

Price rejects EMA9 (the candle closes back below EMA9)

3) Optional filters you can turn on/off

Confirm VWAP on entry TF (ex: only long if current TF close > VWAP)

Relative volume filter (RVOL) (only signal when volume is “decent”)

Session filter (skip first minutes after open, etc.)

Cooldown (prevents alert spam)
